# Controller Patterns

```dart
class FeatureController extends ChangeNotifier with SafeNotifyMixin {
  RequestStatus status = RequestStatus.loading;
  String? errorMessage;

  void fetchData() async {
    try {
      status = RequestStatus.loading;
      safeNotify();
      // ... fetch
      status = RequestStatus.loaded;
      errorMessage = null;
    } catch (e) {
      status = RequestStatus.error;
      errorMessage = e.toString();
    }
    safeNotify();
  }
}
```

- Inject repositories via constructor; call fetch in constructor or explicit method.
- Never call `notifyListeners()` directly — use `safeNotify()`.
- Screens wrap with `ChangeNotifierProvider` + `Consumer` for rebuilds.
- Auth screens (`sign_in_screen`, `register_screen`) use `StatefulWidget` + `setState` — no controller.
